parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent failure of headlight bulbs can cause reduced visibility while driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents and compromising safety.
symptoms: Headlight bulbs burn out frequently
often within a short period of time (e.g.
2-6 months)
affecting low beam or daytime running lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The underlying electrical issue can cause the headlights to malfunction or turn off suddenly, leading to reduced visibility and increased safety risks.
symptoms: Headlights suddenly turn off
daytime running lights and high beams may still function
license plate lights may also be affected
and replacing bulbs does not resolve the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent battery drainage can leave the driver stranded, causing inconvenience and potentially leading to safety issues.
symptoms: Battery drains rapidly
requiring frequent replacements
and the cause of the drainage cannot be identified.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Failure of Low Beam Headlight Bulbs
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent failure of low beam headlight bulbs can significantly reduce visibility while driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Low beam headlight bulbs burn out frequently
often every 2-3 months
with some cases reporting simultaneous failure of both bulbs. The failure can occur without warning
making it essential to check the headlights daily.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, potentially causing serious injury or fatality to passengers.
symptoms: The airbag defect warning light remains on while driving or when the car is on
the airbag light for the right front seat activates
the passenger airbag off sign appears on the dashboard even with an adult passenger in the front seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injury or fatality to passengers.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in an accident
even at moderate speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag sensor can lead to incorrect warnings or failure to deploy the airbag, potentially causing serious injury or fatality to passengers.
symptoms: The passenger airbag off sign appears on the dashboard even with an adult passenger in the front seat
the airbag defect warning light remains on while driving or when the car is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, become stuck in neutral, or roll backwards, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes an abnormal noise
the vehicle fails to start
the vehicle rolls backwards while in park
the vehicle becomes stuck in neutral
the vehicle loses power while driving.
